  "text": "ILM implementation spans three modules: (1) x-pack/plugin/ilm/src/main/ contains the runtime engine \u2014 IndexLifecycleService triggers policy evaluation on cluster state changes and delegates to IndexLifecycleRunner, which uses PolicyStepsRegistry to look up steps and submits ExecuteStepsUpdateTask for cluster state updates. TransportPutLifecycleAction and TransportDeleteLifecycleAction handle CRUD of policies. IndexLifecycleTransition computes state transitions. (2) x-pack/plugin/core/src/main/.../ilm/ holds the model and step framework \u2014 LifecyclePolicy maps phase names to Phase objects, Phase maps action names to LifecycleAction instances, Step is the abstract base class with subtypes ClusterStateActionStep (synchronous cluster state mutation), AsyncActionStep (async external action), AsyncWaitStep (async condition polling), and ClusterStateWaitStep (synchronous condition check). TimeseriesLifecycleType defines the valid phase ordering. IndexLifecycleMetadata is the cluster-state-level custom metadata holding all policies. (3) server/src/.../cluster/metadata/LifecycleExecutionState.java is a record stored per-index in IndexMetadata tracking current step, phase, action, failure info, and timestamps.",
